  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing Hemodialysis and fragmentation of kidney stones</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Al Afia fund charity in Homs is always providing hemodialysis for kidney patients since establishing at August 2006 .during the crises from about 6 years ago a lot of public hospitals went out of service like, Al Watani hospital ,and Ibn Al Waleed hospital in Al Waer area caused by  irreparable damages that happened to it.That added unbearable weight on the charity shoulders .Since the 20 th of February 2014 WHO started to provide our charity with hemodialysis materials (Vistula,tubes,acid,Bicarbonate)  in condition that we have to pay for the sessions and some of the materials (Heparin+Magnesium, vitamin etc...) ,and technician, doctor and hospital fees. On the other hand patients  must pay for  the Epoetin  and their monthly  and interim examination. the number of patents reached till now 255 patients .Those patients need more than 1900 sessions monthly .How ever the number is still rising which might lead that our charity might not be able to take care of all hemodialysis patients by its own .Kindly note that the  number  of sessions during the last 8 months of this year  have reached 13867 hemodialysis patient.WHO had helped us  till this date with 9200 hemodialysis sessions&apos; materials .In the case of accepting to give us this grant, we will provide this service  without taking anything from the patients, making this service  totally free of charge.
Recently we opened Al Afia center for  hemodialysis and kidney&apos;s&apos; stones Fragmentation. we welcome about  60 kidney&apos;stones fragmentation patient monthly and about 255 hemodialysis patient.

we plan in this project  to help 144 hemodialysis  patients with the total of 8729 sessions, the number  of sessions varies from one to another  about 8 sessions  for one patient monthly (1-3 sessions per week) ,as for the 315 kidney&apos;s stones fragmentation patient.  

we will refer all patients  to Al Afia kidney center only.</narrative>
  </description>
